Class ForwardFunction

public abstract class ForwardFunction
extends java.lang.Object
implements AmritaConstants

copyright (c) 2012 e-Amrita - Ing. Giampietro Zedda Turin (Italy)

ForwardFunction

La funzione applicativa rappresenta l'unità elementare funzionale di esecuzione
Dal punto di vista operativo lavora dentro un applet o una finestra JFrame
ed è composta da uno o più form, normalmente da un solo form in funzioni mediamente complesse.
Una funzione può a sua volta richiamare o essere richiamata da altre funzioni.
La base di ogni funzione Forward è la GUI Swing Java, che viene generata in modo generalizzato e viene
quindi replicata in fase di deploy.

Ogni form è composto da un insieme di pannelli relazionati da 1 o più gestori di layout
per realizzare una intergaccia GUI Java comunque complessa, come descritto dalla classe
ForwardForm. Gli oggetti della classe ForwardForm, in collaborazione con ForwardPanel
e ForwardPanelComponent, contengono anche tutti i riferimenti agli oggetti GUI java che compongono
l'interfaccia.
Dal momento che l'intergaccia GUI Swing è l'interfaccia di riferimento, tutte le informazioni
grafiche e di rendering sono già naturalmente ed esaustivamente memorizzate negli stessi.
Il monitor Forward Web, responsabile del deploy su server, interrogherà gli oggetti descrittori
di forward (applicativi e funzionali) e gli oggetti grafici GUI di Swing, per ottenere tutte le
informazioni necessarie a realizzare una interfaccia equivalente in codice HTML puro + eventuale
Java Script dove necessario.

Una delle caratteristiche di progetto più importanti di Forward è la riusabilità, che arriva fino
al singolo pannello. In pratica la definizione di uno specifico pannello, la sua strategia di accesso
ai dati e ogni specifica logica applicativa, sono condivisibili fra funzioni diverse.

L'unità elementare applicativa è invece il pannello descritto dalla classe ForwardPanel
che contiene i campi e gli oggetti grafici per interagire con l'utente.
Ogni pannello può fare riferimento a una strategia di accesso ai dati che lo alimenti e possiede
uno specifico gestiore di layout standard Java.
Il pannello elenca i campi elementari, da db o meno, da gestire, utilizzando oggetti ForwardPanelComponent.
Parallelamente a ogni campo elementare viene associato il corrispondenti componente grafico standard Java
da utilizzare per il rendering, da disporre secondo il gestore di layout scelto.
In alternativa il pannello può dichiarare di ospitare un'altra funzione completa

Tutte le caratteristiche della funzione, dagli oggetti grafici, ai gestori di layout etc.,
sono modellati con le features standard Java, con GUI Swing che possono essere rese una
applicazione funzionante ultilizzando il monitor di Forward GUI per Desktop e successivamente
in ambiente Web con il Monitor GUI per server.

Questo descrittore, ovvero una istanza della classe ForwardFunction, viene utilizzato
in tutti gli ambienti di deploy per generare l'applicazione funzionante.
Le informazioni necessarie vengono ottenute con semplici metodi get().
A tale scopo un oggetto della classe ForwardFunction, con tutti gli oggetti di tutte le classi implicate,
viene serializzato su disco.

Lo stesso descrittore della funzione viene utilizzato, essendo un oggetto java, dal monitor
Forward per Web, in pratica una Servelet generalizzata che genera HTML e codice annesso
a partire sempre dal descrittore della funzione.

Una intera funzione applicativa, descritta da una istanza di questa classe può essere visualizzata
e gestita dentro un pannello di una funzione qualsiasi, che ne deventa un contenitore, esattamente
come il contenitore principale, ovvero JFrame o JApplet.
Ciò permette la completa interoperabilità e riusabilità delle varie funzioni. Un esempio è rappresentato
dall'IDE di sviluppo Forward che, nel pannello centrale, contiene prprio la funzione in definizione,
con tutti i suoi pannelli, completamente indipendente.

ForwardFunction implementa, rende disponibili le variabili di controllo e ne
permette la variazione, del modello MVC rappresentato da Forward.

Tutte le informazioni applicative della funzione, dei pannelli e delle loro relazioni,
oltre che dei campi nei pannelli, sono disponibili al codice applicativo di eccezione.
Tale codice viene collocato in una classe che eredita da ForwardFunction e contiene:

  • La descrizione formale della funzione in forma dichiarativa
  • L'elenco dei pannelli, delle loro relazioni e le modalità di visualizzazione
  • Per ogni pannello la strategia di accesso ai dati, i campi e il loro posizionamento
  • Le logiche standard predefinite da Forward
  • L'attivazione del codice applicativo di eccezione, se non gestibile in modo standard
  • Alle le logiche applicative di eccezione viene assegnato un nome univoco
E' previsto un unico metodo di codice applicativo di eccezione che smisterà, secondo necessità,
verso altri metodi applicativi specifici.

Tali metodi hanno a disposizione solo 3 parametri:

  • system
    Si tratta di un oggetto ForwardSystem.
    Sono disponibili tutte le informazioni di sistema, non applicative,
    di sessione, ambiente, defaulte e di installazione.

    Attraverso l'oggetto system è possibile accedere a tutte le aree di comuni comunicazione previste,
    gestite dalla classe ForwardCommonAreas.
    Ogni area di comunicazione è tipicamente strutturata in parametri/valore.
    Tuttavia il valore, normalmente una stringa, può essere un oggetto generico e quindi utilizzabile
    per gli scopi più diversi, come per esempio cashing o passaggio dati strutturati.

    • Global Common Area
      Contiene informazioni condivise con tutto il server per tutte le applicazioni.
    • Session Common Area
      Contiene informazioni condivise nell'ambito di una stessa sessione utente.
    • Function Common Area
      Contiene informazioni condivise nell'ambito della stessa funzione.
    • Function to function Common Area
      Contiene informazioni condivise fra una funzione chiamante e una chiamata.
      Viene utilizzata per fornire parametri e strutture a una funzione choiamata e per
      permettere a qusta di restituire dei risultati.
  • function
    Si tratta di un oggetto ForwardFunction.
    Sono disponibili tutte le informazioni della funzione correntemente in esecuzione,
    in tutti i suoi aspetti. Attraverso i metodi a disposizione è possibile conoscere le
    caratteristiche della funzione, i diritti di accesso, i pannelli che la compongono
    con tutti i componenti. Di ogni componente è possibile conoscere il valore e modificarlo.
    Sono inoltre disponibili tutte le informazioni della struttura della funzione ed è possibile modificare il comportamento predefinito della stessa.
    E' possibile conoscere l'evento che ha attivato l'esecuzione della logica e l'dentificativo della
    logica per effettuare le attività previste.

  • commonArea Si tratta di un oggetto ForwardCommonAreas.
    Permette di di conoscere e aggiornare informazioni comuni a tutto il server,
    valide solo per la sessione attiva oppure comuni a tutta la funzione applicativa.
    Operativamente si aggiorna o si ottiene un valore a fronte di un nome ed è
    a carico dell'applicativo il casting corretto.
    In realtà è possibile memorizzare nelle varie common aree interi oggetti, secondo le
    più diverse esigenze applicative. Per esempio si possono gestire cash applicative.

ForwardFunction

Constructor

Method Detail

runDeclare

public void runDeclare(DirectivesInfo di)

Run the declare function specification


This method is intended for exclusive internal use by forward monitor, for a correct exception management

declare

public abstract void declare()

Declare function specification


define() contains calls declaring function methods like a documentation script.

Applications function classes must extends ForwardFunction, an abstract class that define
just the abstract method declare().
Forward monitor calls declare() in the initialization process to build function structures.

menuLevelUpdate

public void menuLevelUpdate()
Menu level update.

This method is intended for exclusive internal use by forward monitor.
Menus and submenus are declared by function separately and there is not, at declaring time,
the information of deep level menu.
For each root menu declared, there will be updated any submenu called with its own level, 0-based

BEGIN_FUNCTION_SPECIFICATION

public void BEGIN_FUNCTION_SPECIFICATION(java.lang.String functionName,
                                         java.lang.String title,
                                         EnumForwardFunctionModel model,
                                         EnumLanguage language,
                                         EnumForwardOption... options)

Begin Function Specification And Documentation declaration

It's a marker to delimit a full featured application function declaration.
Informations declared in a not procedural fashion are enough to get the application running.

No matter about technical aspects, fully supported by the monitor forward,
simply you don't care.
They're masked by software layers that make the work for the programmer.
So a FSD appears to be just a documentation script, a list of not
procedural execution rules, only a static descriptor of the function,
structured in own sections.

But the compliance of section to the application model implemented by Forward, doesn't
make the application with limits. It's always possible to access to any part of the
application when it needs.

Parameters:
functionName - the name of the funzion
title - the text in the title bar
model - as a EnumForwardFunctionModel enumeration
language - as a EnumLanguage enumeration
options - as an optional list of EnumForwardOption enumerations

END_FUNCTION_SPECIFICATION

public void END_FUNCTION_SPECIFICATION()

End Function Specification And Documentation declaration

BEGIN_FORM

public void BEGIN_FORM(java.lang.String formName,
                       EnumForwardOption formType,
                       java.lang.String menuBarName)

Begin form declaration

Depict the first step of the function building, the structure of any form
used by function.
Normally a function is built using just one form but for very complex functions may
be better to structure the function with more forms.

The structure is based on java and layout manager standard of java, used to lay panels,
in the main container JFrame or JApplet or in another panel.

A form is implemented with a container like JFrame or JDialog and so can be with
a menu bar attached too. If the input menuBar is null or an empty string or there is no menu declared
with that name for the function, no action is taken.

A form is a set of panels, recursively defined, that contains, in the leaf panel,
java Swing controls, graphic objects like JTextField and so on.
Java graphic controls not elementary like JTree, JList, and JTable, are managed with specific panel types specialized and
already featured

There is a set of specialized set of panels ready to use to manage menus, tre, tabbed panels, properties and so on, to cover the most common application needs.

Each panel can be a container for others panels and use, to lay panels,
java layout managers like BOX_LAYOUT, FLO_LAYOUT, BORDER_LAYOUT.
To lay java swing controls in a leaf panel, named DETAIL the GRID_BAG_LAYOUT
is used instead.

So there is nothing of hidden or different from the normal way to realize java applications.
It should be declared this methos for each level of nesting panels in the form.

Parameters:
formName -
formType - the EnumForwardOption describing the form
menuBarName - as defined by MENU() declarations

PANELS_STRUCTURE

public void PANELS_STRUCTURE(java.lang.String panelName,
                             EnumForwardPanelType panelType,
                             EnumForwardLayout panelLayout,
                             java.lang.String panelNorth,
                             java.lang.String panelCenter,
                             java.lang.String panelSouth,
                             java.lang.String panelEast,
                             java.lang.String panelWest)

Panel form declaring in structure

Constructor specific for panels with layout manager BORDER_LAYOUT

The order of child panels to lay out depends on the BORDER_LAYOUT layout manager.
So sequence order must be NORTH, CENTER, SOUTH, EAST and WEST.
Put a null string in the place holder if the area is to be left empty.

Parameters:
panelName -
panelType - as a EnumForwardPanelType.CONTAINER constant
panelLayout - as a EnumForwardLayout.BORDER_LAYOUT constant
panelNorth - as the panel name to be layied out or a null string if no panel to lay out
panelCenter - as the panel name to be layied out or a null string if no panel to lay out
panelSouth - as the panel name to be layied out or a null string if no panel to lay out
panelEast - as the panel name to be layied out or a null string if no panel to lay out
panelWest - as the panel name to be layied out or a null string if no panel to lay out

BEGIN_PANEL_DETAIL_CONTENT

public void BEGIN_PANEL_DETAIL_CONTENT(java.lang.String panelName,
                                       java.lang.String panelNameDetail)

Begin panel detail contents declaration

After this declaration you are allowed to code COMPONENT() declarations to lay out
GUI components on the panel.

The panel can be previously declared as DETAIL in a PANEL_STRUCTURE() declaration
or coded as a component directly to be layed out as a JPanel component.
Normally the PANEL_STRUCTURE() declaration causes the function panel internal structures
to be created but, when a panel is directly layed out as a normal component, a BEGIN_PANEL_DETAIL_CONTENT
will cause first the same operation too.
So, in the last case, the panel will be inserted in internal structures as a DETAIL panel with a BOX_LAYOUT
manager to be used to lay out all components.

Parameters:
panelName - the internal name of panel
panelNameDetail - the text name of panel as displayed, for example, on tab for tabbed panels

panelTabText - the name of panel as displayed on tab
popUpMenuName - the name of popUp to make active

COMPONENT

public void COMPONENT(javax.swing.JLabel jlabel,
                      java.lang.String controlName,
                      int row,
                      java.lang.String textLabel)

Panel JLabel control declaration

A JLabel Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row and column specified
for the number of cells in horizontal (cellWidth) and in vertical (cellHeight) specified.
In the section PANEL_STRUCTURE it has been specified the layout manager for the panel.
Normally the detail panels contains rows, and the choosen layout manager is GRID_BAG_LAYOUT.
In this case are specified parameters specific for this type of layout.

Any further parameter for the control is set in the section BEGIN_TUNING_LAYOUT,
where it is possible set all native parameters directly on the java object control.
Forward monitor will execute this section to complete the GUI definition.
Here is an example of how code a different minimunSize and toolTip for a JLabel control: 

   getJLabel("Panel1", "LAB01").setMinimunSize(150, 70)
   getJLabel("Panel1", "LAB01").setToolTipText("This is a label")
No operations are required for about getting instance of object control, casting operations and so on.

This way to realize the GUI interface let to take advantage of all features of java with the minimun coding effort.
And then the reference even for the monitor of forward running on the server, is the java graphic object,

Parameters:
jlabel - the swing JLabelobject
controlName -
row -
text - of label

                      java.lang.String textLabel)

Panel JPasswordField control declaration

If a GRID_BAG_LAYOUT manager has been used to lay out the control on the panel, a GridBagConstraints
will be generated and stored at the panel component level.
TUNING_LAYOUT section can get and update the specific constraint and any swing control parameter.

Parameters:
jpasswordField - object
controlName -
row -

initialValue -

COMPONENT

public void COMPONENT(javax.swing.JTextArea jtextArea,
                      java.lang.String controlName,
                      int row,
                      int textAreaRows,
                      int textAreaColumns,
                      int width,
                      int height,
                      boolean maximumSizeToSet,
                      java.lang.String initialValue)

Panel JTextArea control declaration

A JTextArea Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row and column specified
for the number of cells in horizontal (cellWidth) and in vertical (cellHeight) specified.
The JTextArea object will be layed out inside a JScrollBar object with vertical and horizontal
bar just only if it needs.

Notice that it needs to set maximumSizeToSet parameter to true, when the text area is layed out on a panel where
a BOX_LAYOUT layout manager is used. In this case a true value avoid an undesiderable and unexpected
tree expansion in width and heigh. For any other layout manager this doesn't happen.

TUNING_LAYOUT section can get and update the specific constraint and any swing control parameter.

Parameters:
jtextArea - the swing JTextArea object
controlName -
row -
textAreaRows -
textAreaColumns -
width - the width of the JScrollPane used to show as a scrollable object
height - the height of the JScrollPane used to show as a scrollable object
maximumSizeToSet - true to set maximumSize property to width and height set for preferredSize
initialValue -

COMPONENT

public void COMPONENT(javax.swing.JSlider jslider,
                      java.lang.String controlName,
                      int row,
                      int orientation,
                      int min,
                      int max,
                      int initialValue,
                      int majorTickSpacing,
                      int minorTickSpacing,
                      boolean paintTicks,
                      boolean paintLabels,
                      boolean invertedRange,
                      boolean snapToTicks,
                      boolean labelsStandard,
                      int[] ar_valueLabel,
                      java.lang.String[] ar_label,
                      java.lang.String labelNameModel)

Panel JSlider control declaration

This is the constructor for a slider with all properties available.

A JSlider Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row and column specified
for the number of cells in horizontal (cellWidth) and in vertical (cellHeight) specified.
If a GRID_BAG_LAYOUT manager has been used to lay out the control on the panel, a GridBagConstraints
will be generated and stored at the panel component level.
TUNING_LAYOUT section can get and update the specific constraint and any swing control parameter.

Here is an example of JSlider declaration:

   COMPONENT(new(JSlider), "sld_control", 0, 0, 1, 1, 
                                                      new Integer(JSlider.HORIZONTAL),          Orientation
                                                      new Integer(10),                                  Minimum
                                                      new Integer(100),                                 Maximum
                                                      new Integer(30),                                  Initial
                                                      new Integer(20),                                  Major tick spacing
                                                      new Integer(5),                                   Minor tick spacing
                                                      true                                                                      Paint ticks
                                                      true                                                                      Paint Labels
                                                      true                                                                      Values range from higher to lower
                                                      true                                                                      Values selection not continue but with snap to ticks
                                                      true                                                                      Paint label standard with numeric value
                                                      new Integer[]{20, 40, 80},                        Labels values (not significative)
                                                      new String[]{"Low", "Medim", "High"}      Labels strings (not significative)
                                                      "lb_model"                                                                Label name object model for font and color of slider labels (not significative)

Parameters:
jslider - the JSlider object
controlName -
row -
orientation - as JSlider.HORIZONTAL or JSlider.VERTICAL
min -
max -
initialValue -
majorTickSpacing -
minorTickSpacing -
paintTicks - true to paint ticks for majorTickSpacing and minorTickSpacing
paintLabels - true to paint numeric or custom labels after ticks
invertedRange - true to show values range from higher to lower
snapToTicks - true to make selecting values not continue
labelsStandard - true for labels as standard numbers and false for custom labels
ar_valueLabel - the array with numeric values to which assign a personalized label significative if labelsStandard is false
ar_label - the string array with personalized labels significative if labelsStandard is false
labelNameModel - the name of a label component, previously defined, as a model foreground and background color and font significative if labelsStandard is false

                      int min,
                      int max,
                      int initialValue)

A JSlider Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row and column specified
for the number of cells in horizontal (cellWidth) and in vertical (cellHeight) specified.

will be generated and stored at the panel component level.
TUNING_LAYOUT section can get and update the specific constraint and any swing control parameter.

                                                                    new Integer(100),                  Maximum
                                                                    new Integer(30),                   Initial

Panel JSpinner control date declaration

This is the constructor for a spinner of date
To make the date to be formatted and verified, specify an editor mask like, for example, MM/yyyy.
or dd/MM/yyyy
Parameters date can be achieved for example in this way: 
  Date initDate = calendar.getTime();
  calendar.add(Calendar.YEAR, -100);
  Date earliestDate = calendar.getTime();
  calendar.add(Calendar.YEAR, 200);
  Date latestDate = calendar.getTime();
It's possible specify the name of the label regestred for spinner, with no effects if an empty string.
Then the number of columns lets to assign the dimension of the formatted text field of the spinner.
A JSpinner Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row and column specified
for the number of cells in horizontal (cellWidth) and in vertical (cellHeight) specified.
If a GRID_BAG_LAYOUT manager has been used to lay out the control on the panel, a GridBagConstraints
will be generated and stored at the panel component level.
TUNING_LAYOUT section can get and update the specific constraint and any swing control parameter.

                      java.util.Date earliestDate,
                      java.util.Date latestDate,
                      int width)

Panel JSpinner control date declaration

This is the constructor for a spinner of date
To make the date to be formatted and verified, specify an editor mask like, for example, MM/yyyy.
or dd/MM/yyyy
Parameters date can be achieved for example in this way: 
  Date initDate = calendar.getTime();
  calendar.add(Calendar.YEAR, -100);
  Date earliestDate = calendar.getTime();
  calendar.add(Calendar.YEAR, 200);
  Date latestDate = calendar.getTime();
It's possible specify the name of the label regestred for spinner, with no effects if an empty string.
Then the number of columns lets to assign the dimension of the formatted text field of the spinner.
A JSpinner Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row and column specified
for the number of cells in horizontal (cellWidth) and in vertical (cellHeight) specified.
If a GRID_BAG_LAYOUT manager has been used to lay out the control on the panel, a GridBagConstraints
will be generated and stored at the panel component level.
TUNING_LAYOUT section can get and update the specific constraint and any swing control parameter.

Parameters:
spinner - object
controlName -
row -
labelName - for spinner
editor - mask
initDate -
earliestDate -
latestDate -
width -

public void COMPONENT(javax.swing.JPanel jPanel,
                      java.lang.String panelName,
                      int row)




JPanel control declaration

 
 A JPanel Swing control will be laid out on the panel starting at row specified.

 

 This is a convenient method to declare a detail panel as a short cut declaration, directly inside another detail panel,

 without defining previously it by PANELS_STRUCTURE() declaratives.

 

 It there must be a BEGIN_PANEL_DETAIL_CONTENT() for the panel to lay out as a component and there.

 it must be specified the layout manager to use to lay out controls on the panel.

 

 The panel will be automatically resized by java depending on swing controls layed out on.

 No operations are required for about getting instance of object control, casting operations and so on.

 This is the method for minimal parameters specification.

 












Parameters:
jPanel - the swing JPanel object
panelName - 
row -

 This is a convenient method to declare a detail panel as a short cut declaration, directly inside another detail panel,

 without defining previously it by PANELS_STRUCTURE() declaratives.

 

 

 It there must be a BEGIN_PANEL_DETAIL_CONTENT() for the panel to lay out as a component and there.

 it must be specified the layout manager to use to lay out controls on the panel.

 

 No operations are required for about getting instance of object control, casting operations and so on.

 This is the method for full parameters specification.

 

 This way to realize the GUI interface let to take advantage of all features of java with the minimun coding effort.

 And then the reference even for the monitor of forward running on the server, is the java graphic object,

 

 This method allows you to set preferred width and height size and if the maximum size should be to the same value too.

COMPONENT


public void COMPONENT(java.lang.Class boxClass,
                      java.awt.Component glue,
                      java.lang.String controlName,
                      EnumForwardComponent glueType,
                      int row,
                      int width,
                      int heigh)




Space separator control declaration

 

 This constructor lets to declare a java transparent separator between controls and between rows when controls 

 are layed out using the BOX_LAYOUT layout manager.

 The separator is a Box.createXyyy() object and can be a rigid area, as a rectangole, a structure vertical, horizontal

 or, at the end, an object that expands itself both horizontal and vertical (glue).

 For any detailed explaination about glue, struct and rigid area  as separators, please refers to standard Java documentation 

 about BoxLayout

 

 At declaring time, if the separator type is not correct, no action will be taken.

 At execution time, if the panel is not managed by a BOX_LAYOUT layout manager, no action will be taken.

 

 To leave spaces between components it's better to use JBoxRigidArea separator to be sure to leave unmodified the thickness of others row controls.

 

 The input glue component must be an object obtained at the method call like, for example, valid gllue declaration are:
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createHorizontalGlue(), "glue01", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxGlueHorizontal, 7, 0, 0);           
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createHorizontalStrut(10), "glue01", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxStrutHorizontal, 7, 10, 0);              
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createGlue(), "glue01", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxGlue, 7, 3, 0, 0);                                                            
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createRigidArea(new Dimension(10, 20)), "glue01", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxRigidArea, 7, 10, 20);  
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createVerticalGlue(), "glue02", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxGlueVertical, 8, 0, 0);                               
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createVerticalStrut(10), "glue02", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxStrutVertical, 8, 0, 10);                  
 COMPONENT(Box.class, Box.createRigidArea(new Dimension(10, 20)), "glue02", EnumForwardComponent.JBoxRigidArea, 8, 10, 20); 
 
 Note. When JBoxStrutHorizontal, JBoxStrutVertical or JBoxRigidArea are used, widht and heigh will be those in input
 method and not those of the object Box.

 











Parameters:
boxClass - the method marker as an object class that must be Box.class
Component - the Box.CreateX... component
controlName - the name assigned
glueType - must be EnumForwardComponent element among JBoxGlue | JBoxGlueHorizontal | JBoxGlueVertical
row - the row number in the panel, 0-based
width - the BoxRigidArea width or the size of the BoxStrutHorizontal or 0 if not significative
heigh - the BoxRigidArea heigh or the size of the BoxStrutVertical or 0 if not significative

DATA_SOURCE


public void DATA_SOURCE(java.lang.String componentName,
                        java.lang.String ldvName,
                        java.lang.String... ar_columnBound)




Declare the source of data for a component

 Data source is not specified directly as a database table but as a forward logical data view. 

 A logical data view, often named ldv is a simple way to declare complex database access,

 without Sql use.

 

 A logical data view returns a set of rows with and every column has the own name, object and entity table data base definition.

 So the same java column name is assigned by default to every column of a logical data view.

 Automatically the value got by the logical data view is assigned by forward monitor to all controls

 with the same name, in every panel into wich they are declared.
 

 A section DATA_SOURCE is declared for objects like:
 

 
    
  
  • PANEL
    • 
  The panel can be specialized to manage a JTable object, a JList or to be a plain detail panel.
    
  In any case, specifyng an ldv for the panel, the forward monitor is forced to exec it populating fields with
    
  the same name.
  
  • COMBO
    • 
  ComboBox objects are like a normal field and so, through the logical data view of the panel, a value is initially set.
    
  But when the user requires to select a new value by a click, then it's necessary specify a logical data view to show
    
  the desired column and to get all necessary columns values.
    
  Returning back from the comboBox row selection, the forward monitor will store selected columns values in the monitor
    
  internal areas and will update controls in panels if it needs.
    
  
  • LIST
    • 
  Jlist objects are a set of rows  to be populated through the logical data view data.
    
 

 

 Notice that the columns specified are couples of names. The first is the column name as returned by logical data view

 and the second is the name of a control declared, to let the automatic bound and setting by forward monitor.

 If the second name is left to an empty string, is intended that the forward monitor will do the bound using the

 same column name of the logical data view.

 

 Any section DATA_SOURCE can appear anywhere in the function declaring, even before the component declaration.

 












Parameters:
componentName - 
ldvName - 
ar_columnBound - as list of strings containing couples of JavaName and ldv columnBound










DATA_VALUES


public void DATA_VALUES(javax.swing.JList jlist,
                        java.lang.String listName,
                        java.lang.String[] ar_value)




List values declaration

 Are declared values that will be displayed by the list, tipically in the phase of Gui tuning,

 as an array of objects depending on the control type.

 

 The DATA_VALUES declaration must be coded after the CONTROL declaration and hence it's necessary

 specify only the the name assigned to the list

 

 If panel or panel field specified are not defined, no action will be executed.

 












Parameters:
panelName - 
controlName - 
Object - ... value










DATA_VALUES


public void DATA_VALUES(javax.swing.JComboBox jcomboBox,
                        java.lang.String comboBoxName,
                        boolean isFirstElementDefault,
                        java.lang.String[] ar_comboBoxItemValue)




ComboBOx items value declaration

 
 Are declared values that will be displayed by the ComboBox, tipically in the phase of GUI tuning.

 

 The DATA_VALUES declaration must be coded after the COMPONENT() declaration

 

 If the comboBox is not defined, no action will be executed.

 If the first element of items list is specified as the initial value and it doesn't match any following item,

 the first item will be displayed at the first show.

 For any further panel default executed by DO_PANEL_DEFAULT_CONTROLS() no default value will be set.
 

 












Parameters:
jcomboBox - to mark the constructor
comboBoxName - 
isFirstElementDefault - as a boolean true if the first element of ar_comboBoxItemValue is the default value
ar_comboBoxItemValue - a string array with comboBox items value

DATA_VALUES


public void DATA_VALUES(javax.swing.JTree jtree,
                        java.lang.String treeName,
                        java.lang.Object rootObject,
                        java.lang.Object[] ar_nodeRecursive)




Tree values declaration

 

 This is the constructor for a tree data with all options available

 

 All types of data related to tree are managed by own tree model, initialized at the tree declaring.

 Here are required main data that populate the tree model as node text names, optional id key and editable informations.

 

 This method is intend for a compact, exausive declaration of tree nodes, mainly for prototyping purpose and

 as default values too. it's possible to declare the complete tree nodes hierarchy.

 

 For any node declared you can assign a string key identificator to be used by application to immediately

 identify a node. The same key id can be use by DATA_BOUND() section to assign specific user application
 objects to nodes, using that direct key id, instead expensive operations to identify the node.

 Of course application can then clear and populate the tree with database data or something else.

 Any node user data object data must be stored as ForwardTreeUserObject object as forward keep necessary 

 data during the node life cycle.

 For prototyping purpose it's enaugh to manage text only and thereby will be automatically created all necessary

 ForwardTreeUserObject objects.

 DATA_BOUND() section, optionally, lets to assign to each node declared a specific applicationuser object

 that overrides the standard ForwardTreeUserObject, string based, automatically generated and assigned to the node.

 

 The DATA_VALUES() declaration must be coded after the tree COMPONENT() declaration.

 

 Here an example of recursive data tree hierarchy declaration:
 DATA_VALUES(new JTree(), "tr_tree01", "Root"
                                        new Object[]{new Object[]{"Node1", "0-0"}                       // Node1 leaf 
                                                    ,new Object[]{"Node2", "0-1",                       // Node2 folder 
                                                                           new Object[]{"Node21", "0-2-0"               // .. 
                                                                                       ,"Node22", "0-2-1"               // ..
                                                                                       ,"Node23", "0-2-2"               // ..
                                                                                       ,"Node24", "0-2-3"               //      Nodes child of Node2  
                                                                                       ,"Node25", "0-2-4"               // ..
                                                                                       ,"Node26", "0-2-5"               // ..
                                                                                       ,"Node27", "0-2-6"               // ..
                                                                                       }
                                                                                                                          
                                                                 }
                                                    ,new Object[]{"Node3", "0-2", true}                 // Node3 folder with first service child automatically inserted
                                                    ,new Object[]{"Node4", "0-2",                       // Node4 folder  
                                                                           new Object[]{"Node41", "0-4-0"                       // ..
                                                                                       ,"Node42", "0-4-1"                       // ..
                                                                                       ,"Node43", "0-4-2"                       // Nodes child of Node4 
                                                                                       ,"Node44", "0-4-3"                       // .
                                                                                       ,"Node45", "0-4-4"                       // ..
                                                                                       }
                                                                 }
                                                    }
 
 
 If the tree specified is not defined, no action will be executed.

 












Parameters:
jtree - just to mark the method, not used
treeName - the internal name assigned to tree
rootObject - as a string object rapresenting the root node
ar_NodeRecursive - as a recursive objects array describing the tree hierarchy as showed in the example










DATA_VALUES_BOUND


public void DATA_VALUES_BOUND(javax.swing.JTree jtree,
                              java.lang.String treeName,
                              java.lang.String[] ar_idKey,
                              ForwardTreeUserObject[] ar_objDataBound)




Declare application data bound for each node, to be bound to the tree

 

 Thi is an optional declaration of specific user objects nodes to be bound to tree nodes.

 By default, in the DATA_VALUES() section, a ForwardTreeUserObject object have been created

 for each node, with the only text property. In this way it's possible to bind any user application objects,

 with the constraint that they must inherits form ForwardTreeUserObject.

 

 The size of input arrays must be the same but no exception occurs if not.

 












Parameters:
jtree - the JTree object to qualify the constructor
treeName - name
ar_idKey - as a String array of id node keys as declared in DATA_VALUES() section.
ar_objDataBound - as a ForwardTreeUserObject objects array bound to nodes identified by ar_idKey.

 The menu item is declared as always as a menu bar item, the most general declaration.

 The scope is to change the aspect and the behaviour of a menu just changing its type.
 A JMenuItem object will be created too.

menuItemCaption -

Begin function tuning

 

 This section allows you to code declarative statements to customize some functional aspects,

 related to the overall function or the specific component layed out on a panel.

 Actually it's possible to specify all declaratives below:
 TABLE_HELP()
 TABLE_CAPTION()
 FUNCTION_CALLABLE()
 COMPONENT_LDV_TO_EXEC()
 COMPONENT_LOOKUP_FUNCTION()
 COMPONENT_LOOKUP_RULE_TABLE()
 COMPONENT_OPTION()<7pre>
 Please refer to related declarative documentation for any detail.

public void END_FUNCTION_TUNING()




End function tuning 

 It's just a marker for the on of section

 






















FUNCTION_CALLABLE


public void FUNCTION_CALLABLE(java.lang.String functionClassName,
                              java.lang.String[] parmNamesRequired,
                              java.lang.String[] parmNamesReturned)




Enables a function to be automatically callable.

 

 The forward monitor allows you to call an enabled function by means of

 a specific function key, that starts a system function with all allowed functions.

 Here your'e allowed to declare a callabl functions, with parameters required and retirned.

 

 No control will be done at declaration time.

 












Parameters:
functionClassNames - as a string array of function class names
parmNamesRequired - as a string array with two token for each element, the first token as the variable or GUI component name

 in the caller function with the item key, the second with the parameter name rquired by called lookup function.
parmNamesReturned - as a string array with two token for each element, the first token as the variable or GUI component name
 in the caller function, the second with the parameter name returned by called lookup function.










TABLE_HELP


public void TABLE_HELP(int numTableHelpTechnical,
                       int numTableHelpEndUser)




Sets the help rule table for function, panel and component, HTML help

 

 The forward monitor allows you to show a localized help at function level, panel level

 and single component layed out the panel.
 
 Any help can have a technical target or a functionally target.

 

 The table item key is panelName + ":" + componentName 
 If panelName = componentName = "", that's a function level help
 If componentName = "", that's a panel level help
 Otherwise is panel component level help.

 












Parameters:
numTableHelpTechnical - as the number of forward table with technical helps for the function
numTableHelpEndUser - as the number of forward table with end user helps for the function










TABLE_CAPTIONS


public void TABLE_CAPTIONS(int numTableCaptions)




Sets the forward table for all localized function captions.

 

 The forward monitor, at the initialization time, sets all captions to the values coded at declaration time. 

 If a different localization is required, the input table number will be used to get all function captions in

 the new language, if any.
 

 Furthermore, afterward if customizations by user/function/component/language are effective, customized values will
 be used instead.>br>
 

 It should be coded a rule table for each function.

 The item key must be panelName:X:componentName

 Where X is an ordinal of EnumForwardCaptionCustomization enumeration.

 When componentName is a null string, the caption is at the panel level, according to X value.

 












Parameters:
numTableCaptions - as the number of forward table with captions for the function










COMPONENT_LOOKUP_RULE_TABLE


public void COMPONENT_LOOKUP_RULE_TABLE(java.lang.String componentName,
                                        int numRuleTable,
                                        java.lang.String[] parmNamesReturned)




Sets the modality of the lookup rule table selection function activation with minimal specifications. 

 

 The lookup function that realizes the selection of a rule table item needs to code parameters

 required and returned by means of PARM_REQUIRED() and PARM_RETURNED() declarations.

 Actually it needs the numTable and language and returns the item key and the description.

 

 Required NumTable and language are automatically supplied to the function by forward monitor.

 Informations for returned parameters are described by the input parameter,  an array of strings 

 where each element contains two substrings:

 The first is the component name in the application function caller, as a variable or GUI control name.

 The second is the parameter name required by called application, defined in the called function by means of a PARM_RETURNED() declaration.

 

 The forward monitor, automatically will set all parameters required by called function with data of caller function

 and, after the item selection, all parameters returned by called function, in the caller function
 

 The lookup function used will be the standard forward function FunctionLookUpRuleTable.

 

 If the component has been not defined in any panel, no action will be taken.
 












Parameters:
componentName - as the GUI component name to enable for the lookup rule table selection function activation
 in the caller function with the item key, the second with the parameter name rquired by called lookup function.
parmNamesReturned - as a string array with two token for each element, the first token as the variable or GUI component name
 in the caller function, the second with the parameter name returned by called lookup function.

 Required parameters are automatically supplied to the function by forward monitor.

 Returned parameters are automatically set by forward monitor in the caller function.

 Informations for required and returned parameters are described by input parameter, two array of strings

 The second is the parameter name required or returned by called application, defined in the called function

COMPONENT_LDV_TO_EXEC


public void COMPONENT_LDV_TO_EXEC(java.lang.String componentName,
                                  java.lang.String ldv,
                                  java.lang.String[] columnNamesKeyRequired,
                                  java.lang.String[] columnNamesReturned)




Sets the logical data view name linked to the component to be executed. 

 

 When for a component has been set COMPONENT_CTRL_EXISTS_LDV_TODO or COMPONENT_CTRL_UNEXISTS_LDV_TODO

 options, the PANEL_CONTROLS or the PANEL_CONTROLS_EXISTENCE_ENTITY action executes the logical data view

 indicated by this declaration.

 

 The purpose is to control the existence or not existence in a legacy table and, optionally, to set

 function application variables or GUI controls, with column values obtained by the logical data view.

 

 To run properly, the logical data view needs key colum values to be set with the content of function

 variables or function GUI controls, as described by columnNamesKeyRequired parameter.

 

 So, required parameters are automatically supplied to the logical data view by forward monitor.

 Returned logical data view columns are automatically used by forward monitor to set  function

 variables or function GUI controls.

 

 Informations for required parameters and returned columns are described by input parameter, two array of strings 

 where each element contains two substrings:

 The first is the component name in the function, as a variable or GUI control name.

 The second is the column name required or returned by the logical data view.

 

 The forward monitor, automatically will set all key columns required by the logical data view with data of caller function

 and, after the logical data view execution, all function data with columns values of the logical data view.
 

 If the compment name specified is not a valid variable name or a GUI control name, no action will be taken.
 












Parameters:
componentName - as the GUI component name to enable for the lookup rule table selection function activation
ldv - the logical data view name to be executed
columnNamesKeyRequired - as a string array with two token for each element, the first token as the variable or GUI component name

 in the function, the second with the key column name required by the logical data view to be properly executed.
columnNamesReturned - as a string array with two token for each element, the first token as the variable or GUI component name
 in the caller function, the second with the column name to be used to set the function component.

COMPONENT_CTRL


public void COMPONENT_CTRL(java.lang.String componentName,
                           EnumForwardOption ctrlTypeToDo,
                           java.lang.Object... ctrlParms)




Sets a control to be executed on a panel component

 

 This declaration causes the forward monitor to execute the input control type,

 during controls at the panel level.

 

 The type of objects depends on the type of control to be executed and on the type of GUI component.

 

 Following control types are without obects control parameters specification:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_EXISTS_LDV 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_UNEXISTS_LDV 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_MANDATORY 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_UPPERCASE 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_LOWERCASE 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_ALPHABETIC 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_NUMERIC
        COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE

 

 When COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE has been specified it must be coded a COMPONENT_CTRL_MASK declarative too, 

 with a valid date mask as yyyMMdd, dd-MM-yyy etc.

 

 Following control types must be coded with a single numeric object parameter:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_EXISTS_TABLE 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_UNEXISTS_TABLE 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_SIZE_MAX                     
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_SIZE_MIN                     
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_INT_MAX     
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_INT_MIN     
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_DEC_MAX     
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_DEC_MIN     
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_MAX                 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_MIN

 

 Following control types must be coded with a single text object parameter:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_MASK 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_VALUE_MAX 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_VALUE_MIN  
        COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE_MAX 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE_MIN 

 

 When COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE_MAX or COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE_MIN has been specified it must be coded a COMPONENT_CTRL_MASK declarative too, 

 Valid  characters masks for Date are supported by standard java DateFormat and are, for example:
yyyy
MM
MMM
dd
 
 So, for a complete could be yyyMMdd, dd-MM-yyy etc.

 

 Valid mask characters formatted field not date are all values supported by standard java MaskFormatter:
#       Any valid number, uses Character.isDigit .
'       Escape character, used to escape any of the special formatting characters.
U       Any character ( Character.isLetter ). All lowercase letters are mapped to upper case.
L       Any character ( Character.isLetter ). All upper case letters are mapped to lower case.
A       Any character or number ( Character.isLetter or Character.isDigit )
?       Any character ( Character.isLetter ).
        Anything.
H       Any hex character (0-9, a-f or A-F).

So, for a complex phone number entry field, you could use a mask like: "(###) ###-####"
and for a field with decimal could be ##.0 

 
 Following control types must be coded with two text object parameter:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_VALUE_RANGE  
        COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE_RANGE

 

 When COMPONENT_CTRL_DATE_RANGE has been specified it must be coded a COMPONENT_CTRL_MASK declarative too, 

 with a valid date mask as yyyMMdd, dd-MM-yyy etc.

 

 Following control types must be coded with two numeric integer object parameter:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_TEXT_SIZE_RANGE
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_INT_RANGE 
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_DEC_RANGE 

        

 Following control types must be coded with two numeric object parameter:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_NUMERIC_VALUE_RANGE

        

 Following control types must be coded with an unlimited number of object parameter:
        COMPONENT_CTRL_VALUES

        












Parameters:
componentName - as the GUI component name to be controlled
ctrlTypeToDo - as an EnumForwardOption enumeration starting with COMPONENT_CTRL
ctrlParms - as an Object array with the content depending on ctrlTypeToDo










BEGIN_LAYOUT_TUNING


public void BEGIN_LAYOUT_TUNING()




Begin layout tuning

 There are two types of layout tuning:
 
    
 
  •  On own specific forward data, function depending
 
  •  Directly on bnative java graphic objects parameters
 

 All panel declared and all CONTROL  in the section PANEL_CONTENT let to make running a

 minimal graphic interface declaring just a few parameters and using default values for any else.

 Any further parameter for the control can be set in the section CONTROLS_ADJUSTMENT.

 

 In this section it is possible set all native parameters directly on the java object object.

 The java object it's a JComponent object JPanel, JLabel and so on.

 It's available a generic method to get any component getJComponent() but the caller must cast it.

 And then it's possible to use specialized methods to get panel and controls.

 

 Forward monitor will execute this section to complete the GUI definition.

 Here is an example of how code a different minimunSize and toolTip for a JLabel control:
 
   getJPanel("Panel1").setSize(300, 500)                                                // Java method
   getJLabel("Panel1", "LAB01").setMinimunSize(150, 70)                         // Java method
   getJLabel("Panel1", "LAB01").setToolTipText("This is a label")                       // Java method
 

 No operations are required for about getting instance of object control, casting operations and so on.

 It's supported a version without the panel specification, because all names in forward are uniques.

 
   getJLabel("LAB01").setToolTipText("This is a label")
 

 

 This way to realize the GUI interface let to take advantage of all features of java with the minimun

 coding effort.

 And then the reference even for the monitor of forward running on the server, is the java graphic object,

 the natural and exaustive store of all informations.
 
 

 

 Forward populates automatically the panel through the execution of the
 strategy data access and setting all values of panel controls.

 

 The populating process sets the correct value for choice field, like

 check box o option goup like group button.

 

 Only controls with the same name are set. The name must be the same name 

 defined in the centralyzed dictionary as a metaField.
 The name is the same for the bean class used to manage a single database

 entity.

 






















END_LAYOUT_TUNING


public void END_LAYOUT_TUNING()




End layout tuning

 It's just a marker for the on of section

 






















BEGIN_EVENTS


public void BEGIN_EVENTS()




Begin events behaviour declaration

 Starts the section declaring all behaviours of the application to events

 and all events are declared using the ON_EVENT section

 

 It's necessary to declare a ON_EVENT section for each event.

 Each event declared describes a own action to be executed when the event occurred.

 This kind of actions are available without coding by Forward and are enaugh in the most

 common cases. They are standard actions in forward applications

 

 However it's possible to gain the full control of events by coding a own event management

 in the application method declared in the ON_EVENT_OTHER section.

 Such a method is a generic reusable application method able to know and modify every bit of 

 the application currently running.

 The method declared by ON_EVENT_OTHER is executed by the forward monitor when no

 event occurred has been trapped and honorated by any ON_EVENT declared.

 

 The events are all standard events defined for java Swing application like those related to 

 ActionListener as ActionPerformed or FocusListener and so on.






















BEGIN_ACTIONS_GROUPS


public void BEGIN_ACTIONS_GROUPS()




Begin groups of actions declaration

 Starts the section declaring all groups of actions identified by a group name.

 

 A group of actions is conceptually the same thing of a method or a routine.

 The difference is that actions declared in the group are not programming instructions

 but model declaring statement.






















END_EVENTS


public void END_EVENTS()




End event behaviour declaration

 It's simply a marker to make clear the declaration.





















END_ACTIONS_GROUPS


public void END_ACTIONS_GROUPS()




Ends groups of actions declaration

 It's only a marker with no effects.

COMPONENT_PROPERTY_DEFAULT


public void COMPONENT_PROPERTY_DEFAULT(EnumForwardComponent componentType,
                                       java.lang.String propertyName,
                                       java.lang.Class propertyValueClass,
                                       java.lang.Object propertyValue)




Component property default declaration

 Declare a default property to be applied to all Swing JComponent of specific type.

 

 A component could be a JPanel implemented by the PANEL_STRUCTURE section or a

 JButton, implemented by the CONTROL section and so on.

 Forward model function declaring uses all java swing properties at the definition time,

 with no wrapper, no classes specialized and so on. It use just native java Swing controls,

 to carry on all properties using native java structure.

 All forward classes let just to describe the application structure and additional applicative data.
  
 

 So, to make the function light and generalized, and to avoid to redefines standard java swing properties

 inside forward, all not default properties can be declared just specifying the name of component name, property 

 and value.

 The property name must be specified beginning with capital letter.

 

 The forward monitor will use java reflection to set properties declared dynamically letting a chance

 to runtime tuning and personalizations.

 












Parameters:
componentType - the EnumForwardComponent constant
propertyName - 
propertyValueClass - 
propertyValue -

 with no wrapper, no classes specialized and so on. It use just native java Swing controls,

 to carry on all properties using native java structure.

 All forward classes let just to describe the application structure and additional applicative data.
  
 

 So, to make the function light and generalized, and to avoid to redefines standard java swing properties

 inside forward, all not default properties can be declared just specifying the name of component name, property 

 and value.

 The property name must be specified beginning with capital letter.

 to runtime tuning and personalizations.

PARM_REQUIRED


public void PARM_REQUIRED(java.lang.String parmNameRequired,
                          java.lang.Object parmInitial)




Function parameter required to function declaration

 Declare a parameter name required for the correct running of the function

 when the function is started by another function.

 

 A parameter name is the name assigned to a fuction variable declared with the same name.
 
 The variable will be automatically created as it was explicitely created by VAR() declaration.

 

 A parameter could be, for example a customer code, to be assigned to a GUI control as default,

 or to access data using a logical data view.

 












Parameters:
parmNameRequired - 
parmInitial - the parameter object with initial value










PARM_RETURNED


public void PARM_RETURNED(java.lang.String parmNameReturned,
                          java.lang.Object parmInitial)




Function parameter returned by function declaration

 Declare a single parameter returned by the current to the caller function.

 

 When a function is started by another function, often the called function returns a value

 or a set of values.
 
 For example a called function called to select a customer from a list, could return back

 to caller a customer code and other select data

 

 But a called function could be return back to caller a structured set o data too. Thus it can

 return back just an object of an applicative class, to have the maximum in terms of flexibility.

 












Parameters:
parmNameReturned - 
parmInitial - the parameter object with initial value










VAR


public void VAR(java.lang.String varName,
                java.lang.Object varInitial)




Variable declaration

 Declare a variable for the current function with the scope function.

 The variable will be allocated at execution time using the initial value

 

 The type of variable, through its class, is set by input initial value, mandatory.

 

 Notice that variables for each table columns are automatically created

 at table definition time.

 












Parameters:
varName - as the name of variable
varInitial - as an Object value the initial value of variable










VAR

                java.lang.String varName,
                java.lang.Object varInitial)




Variable declaration with scope

 Declare a variable for the current function.

 The variable will be allocated at execution time using the initial value

 

 The type of variable, through its class, is set by input initial value, mandatory.

 

 Notice that variables for each table columns are automatically created

 at table definition time.

 












Parameters:
varScope - as the EnumForwardScope scope of the variable
varName - as the name of variable
varInitial - as an Object value the initial value of variable

getFunctionId


public java.lang.String getFunctionId()




Gets the function identification code.

 

 When a caller function declare a START_FUNCTION() action,

 an identification code is also coded.

 When the forward monitor starts a new function due a FUNCTION_START()

 must be executed, sets the function identifier.

 

 This function code is used by forward monitor to properly detect the logic to activate

 on return from the called function.

 

 Normally it should be enaugh the function name called for identification purposes but

 may be that the same function is started as result of different conditions and so it's
 necessary to identify exactly wich.
 













Returns:
the functionId

 When the forward monitor starts a new function due a FUNCTION_START()

 must be executed, sets the function identifier.

 

 This function code is used by forward monitor to properly detect the logic to activate

 on return from the called function.

 

 Normally it should be enaugh the function name called for identification purposes but

 may be that the same function is started as result of different conditions and so it's
 necessary to identify exactly wich.

getCallableFunctionParmsRequired


public java.lang.String[] getCallableFunctionParmsRequired(java.lang.String functionName)




Gets all parameters required to the function potentially callable by function.

 

 It will be returned a string array.

 Each element contains two token.

 The first token is the variable or GUI control name in the caller function and the second

 token is the parameter name to be set in the called function, declared by a PARM_REQUIRED() declaration.

 

 If the function has been not declared as callable, no action will be taken.

 













Returns:
the string  array of required parameters










getCallableFunctionParmsReturned


public java.lang.String[] getCallableFunctionParmsReturned(java.lang.String functionName)




Gets all parameters returned by the function.

 

 It will be returned a string array.

 Each element contains two token.

 The first token is the variable or GUI control name in the caller function to be set and the second

 token is the parameter name  declared by a PARM_RETURNED() declaration in the called function

 to be used as input to set in the caller function the variable or GUI control.

 

 If the function has been not declared as callable, no action will be taken.

 













Returns:
the string  array of returned parameters










getMessage


public java.lang.String getMessage(java.lang.String messageCode,
                                   EnumMessageType messageType,
                                   EnumLanguage messageLanguage)




Gets the message coded

 

 
 Returns the localized message and, if not found, the message code between "??".

 

 The message key is the message type as a prefix MW, MI, DG, DB, EI, ET, EF, TC followed by a numeric string value of 5 digits size.

 There is a forward table for each message type.

 Depending on the message type, it will be read a specific messages table.

 Every table contains both system messages and application function messsages.

 Application function messages start from the code 10000

 












Parameters:
messageCode - the numeric string, five digits to identify the message
messageType - a EnumMessageType enumeration with the type of message
messageLanguage - a EnumLanguage enumeration for the message language










getMessage


public java.lang.String getMessage(java.lang.String messageCode,
                                   EnumMessageType messageType)




Gets the message coded

 

 
 Returns the localized message and, if not found, the message code between "??".

 

 The message key is the message type as a prefix MW, MI, DG, DB, EI, ET, EF, TC followed by a numeric string value of 5 digits size.

 There is a forward table for each message type.

 Depending on the message type, it will be read a specific messages table.

 Every table contains both system messages and application function messsages.

 Application function messages start from the code 10000

 

 The language is that declared by function.

 












Parameters:
messageCode - the numeric string, five digits to identify the message
messageType - a EnumMessageType enumeration with the type of message

isFunctionLookup


public boolean isFunctionLookup()




Gets if the function is a lookup function.

 

 A lookup function is a function automatically started by forward monitor on a GUI control dblClick.

 The GUI component must declare a COMPONENT_LOOKUP_FUNCTION or a COMPONENT_LOOKUP_RULE_TABLE statement.

 When a lookup function is declared to be activated, the forward monitor will automatically manage all issues related to the

 parameters required and returned setting.

 













Returns:
the isLookupFunction

 When a lookup function is declared to be activated, the forward monitor will automatically manage all issues related to the

 parameters required and returned setting.

getVarValue


public java.lang.Object getVarValue(java.lang.String varName)




Returns the current value of the variable in the runtime forward monitor, at the function level scope.
 

 This method returns a generic object containing the value and so it needs to be casted invoking it.

 It's a way to set complex and structured parameters, organized by means of an application object, 

 with the desired visibility.

 To avoid undesiderable exceptions and the casting operation, specific variable

 type dependent methods are available, like getValueString() getValueInt and so on.

 












Parameters:
varName - 

Returns:
the object var value

getValue


public java.lang.Object getValue(java.lang.String name)




Returns the current Object value of the variable name at function scope level or of the GUI control name.
 

 The name can be the name of a declared variable with VAR(), an implicit automatically created

 column variable for a table or, at the end, the name of a control declared in any panel.

 If the name is of a swing object, will be returned an object with the value compatible with the GUI object,
 as an object String, Integer, Double, Float, Boolean, Color and Date.
       
 

 If the name is of a variable not defined or if is defined but not visible for the scope or,

 at the end, it's defined with of a different type, returns null.

 












Parameters:
name - the name of a GUI control or of a variable declared by VAR() or automatically created

Returns:
the value object or null if no GUI control and no variable has been defined with the same name

setValue


public void setValue(java.lang.String componentOrVar,
                     java.lang.Object valueObject)




Sets the GUI control value or the variable value.
 

 The name must be the name of a control declared in any panel or of a variable declared by VAR().

 First, it will be verified if the input name is of a variable declared name and, if not, of a GUI control.

 The object value type must be compatible with the GUI component or the variable name,
 as an object Boolean, String, Integer, Double, Float and so on.
     
 

 If the name is not of a component and neither of a variable no action will be taken

 If the object value type is wrong no action will be taken

 












Parameters:
componentOrVar - the name of a GUI control component or of a variable
valueObject - the value to be set

 The variable name can be the name of a declared variable with VAR(), an implicit automatically created

 column variable for a table or, at the end, the name of a control declared in any panel.

 If the variable name is of a swing object with a current float value, will be returned the float value.
     
 

 If the variable is not defined or if is defined but not visible for the scope or,

 at the end, it's defined with of a different type, returns null.

 












Parameters:
String - varName

Returns:
the Float value

factoryGetInstanceInnerOnEvent


public forward.ForwardFunction.InnerOnEvent factoryGetInstanceInnerOnEvent()




Returns an instance of the internal class describinig an event.

 






















ACTION


public void ACTION(ForwardDoParms... actionsCoded)




Perform unconditionally an action
 
 
 Actions are ranked by EnumForwardAction, implemented by methods starting by DO, and can be automatically activated by declaring an action

 on a ON_EVENT() or invoking a ACTION() directive in any application reusable methos.

 

 In the first case the activation is made automatically by the forward monitor when the event specified occurs.

 In the second case the activation is fully indipendent and piloted only by specific user java application code logic.

 Furthermore, the user java application code can itself be activated by an ON_EVENT() declaration and

 phisically the code (a normal java method) can be coded in the same class declaring the function (a ForwardFunction object)

 or in any other class configutated runtime by forward monitor.

 

 This logic execution model lets to configure runtime whith no coding wich elementary code to execute, making

 the application like a big puzzle where any piece can be changed without to modify the shape.
 
 

 As final result forward realize an applicative behaviour that can be completely configuration dependent and 

 even any bit of code fully reusable.

 The application model and any user application code can be deployed and executed in the web context, by the specific

 monitor (a specialized servelet), whith no changes.
 

 For example you could code an ACTION
 that under specific circumstances causes the refresh of

 a panel, the execution of a logica data view or discard a row in table under loading.
 

 Here one example:

 

 
 ON_EVENT(EnumForwardEvent.value, DO_REFRESH("fieldName")
 












Parameters:
action - do to
object - parameters depending on action type










DO_PANEL_DEFAULTS_INITIAL


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_DEFAULTS_INITIAL(java.lang.String... panelNames)




Sets panel components to the declared default

 

 For all elementary components layed out on the panel, will be applied the declared default

 When no default has been declared the component value will be set to space or zero depending on the type.

 

 If the panel has be not declared by function, no action will be taken.

 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to which apply defaults










DO_PANEL_DEFAULTS_USER


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_DEFAULTS_USER(java.lang.String panelName,
                                             java.lang.String methodName)




Call a user default method for the panel

 

 Application default logics are coded in a user declared method.

 The method will be called on demand by aan ACTION() rirective or by an ON_condition() event.

 

 If the panel has be not declared by function, no action will be taken.

 If the method has be not declared by function, no action will be taken.

 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to which apply defaults










DO_PANEL_POPULATE_FROM_DB


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_POPULATE_FROM_DB(java.lang.String panelName)




Populates the panel using the logical data view, if any.

 

 If no DATA_SOURCE() has been declared at function declaration level for the panel, 
 specifying the logical data view to use, no action will be taken.

 

 The logical data view will be executed and row data column values will be used to update

 swing controls declared by panel.

 

 For about controls like combobox, list, and table, when a logical data view has been

 declared, will be populated too.

 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to wich apply defaults










DO_PANEL_POPULATE_FROM_DB


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_POPULATE_FROM_DB(java.lang.String panelName,
                                                java.lang.String ldvClassName)




Populates the panel using the input logical data view.

 

 If the logical data view is not defined no action will be taken. 
 

 The logical data view will be executed and row data column values will be used to update

 swing controls declared by panel.

 

 For about controls like combobox, list, and table, when a logical data view has been

 declared, will be populated too.

 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to wich apply defaults
ldvClassName - the logical data view class name to be use to populate the panel










DO_PANEL_CONTROLS


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_CONTROLS(java.lang.String panelName,
                                        java.lang.String methodName)




Executes all controls in sequence
 

 It will be executed the sequence of controls below 
 CONTROLS_FORMAL
 CONTROLS_EXISTENCE_ENTITY
 CONTROLS_EXISTENCE_RULE_TABLE
 CONTROLS_USER 
 

 User controls will be executed only if previosly controls ended with no error.

 Overall errors detected will be showed toghether by means of the forward monitor.

 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to control
methodName - the name of the application method, not active if an empty string










DO_PANEL_CONTROLS_FORMAL


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_CONTROLS_FORMAL(java.lang.String panelName)




Executes formal controls for components layed out by panel

 

 They are controls for about:
 
 Numeric/not numeric
 Max and Min value
 Range
 Decimal places 
 Decimal value
 

 All controls, to be effective, must be declared for the component by means of the

 COMPONENT_OPTIONS() declarative.
 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to control

DO_PANEL_CONTROLS_USER


public ForwardDoParms DO_PANEL_CONTROLS_USER(java.lang.String panelName,
                                             java.lang.String methodName)




Executes panel application user context controls.

 

 This action allow you to declare an application method responsible for

 controls among controls in the panel or others panels

 

 If the application method is not declared by function, no action will be taken.

 

 The input application method can query the state of all function, and

 the value of all declared controls.

 It must call the system setActivePanelContextControlsGood() with a
 value of true or false, to inform the forward monitor of the result of controls.

 












Parameters:
panelName - the panel name to wich apply defaults
methodName - the application method name to be executed

DO_EXEC_METHOD


public ForwardDoParms DO_EXEC_METHOD(java.lang.String methodName,
                                     java.lang.Object... parms)




Execute a reusable application method with application logic

 

 To increment reusability and so to share even little bit of code, it's optionally possible

 to declare an unlimited number of parameters for the method.

 The method can then get parameters through the variable parms available by the action descriptor

 of the ForwardSystem object.
 

 To get parameters the method called must perform something so:
   Object parms[] = s.getActiveDoParms().parms












Parameters:
methodName - the method name to execute
parms - as an optional  sequence of objects, normally simple strings, available in the called method










DO_EXEC_ACTIONS_ON_EVENT


public ForwardDoParms DO_EXEC_ACTIONS_ON_EVENT(EnumForwardEvent actionEvent,
                                               java.lang.String componentName)




Execute all actions already declared for a component name and an event.

 

 To increment reusability at the model level and so to share even little bit of declarations, 

 you are allowed to execute all actions coded by a specific declared event.

 If the event is not declared for the component no action will be taken.

 












Parameters:
groupActionsName - the group name of actions
actions - as a sequence of specific actions to exec

 If the group name is not defined no action will be taken.

DO_SKIP_EVENT_ACTIONS


public ForwardDoParms DO_SKIP_EVENT_ACTIONS(java.lang.String actionSkipId)




Stops the execution of all actions still to be executed, for the current event.

 

 May be useful not to exec further declared actions due application conditions.

 For example after the run of a logical data view with non record found you are allowed

 to stop any further action by coding ON_EVENT(EnumForwardEvent.ON_LDV_GET_NO_ROWS, DO_STOP_EVENT_ACTIONS())
 

 Because of several events could need to stop execution under specific events, an id can be specified to

 make any condition unique.

 












Parameters:
actionSkipId - the id that must be active to make the stop effective.

 an empty value means no id test.










DO_SKIP_SET_ID


public ForwardDoParms DO_SKIP_SET_ID(java.lang.String actionSkipId)




Sets the id to be tested to make the DO_STOP_EVENT_ACTIONS action effetctive.

 












Parameters:
actionStopId - the id that must be active to make the stop effective.
